Today I learned how to search for files and directories in linux using the find command.
  ##commands practiced
  -find . -name "filename" : search file by name
  -find . -iname "filename" : case-insensitive search
  -find . type  f : find only files
  -find . type d : find only directories
  -find . -name "*txt" : search files by extension
  -find . -delete : delete all fikes found
  -find . -exec <command> {} \; : execute command on found files
